FastPressElement - Class in io.ashton.fastpress.client.fast
GWT Implementation influenced by Google's FastPressElement: https://developers.google.com/mobile/articles/fast_buttons Using Code examples and comments from: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/9596807/converting-gwt-click-events-to-touch-events The FastPressElement is used to avoid the 300ms delay on mobile devices (Only do this if you want to ignore the possibility of a double tap - The browser waits to see if we actually want to double top) The "press" event will occur significantly fast (around 300ms faster).
